</b></p>
<p><b>  Persons with albinism 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Report of the Office of the United Nations High 
Commissioner for Human Rights</b>*<b> 
</b></p>
<p><i>Summary 
</i></p>
<p> This preliminary report of the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for 
Human Rights on the attacks and discrimination against persons with albinism is submitted 
pursuant to Human Rights Council resolution 23/13 of 13 June 2013. 
</p>
<p> In some communities, erroneous beliefs and myths influenced by superstition put 
the security and life of persons with albinism at risk. 
</p>
<p> OHCHR has received information from various countries on cases of killings and 
dismembering of persons with albinism for ritual purposes. It has also collected 
information on the multiple and intersecting forms of discrimination persons with albinism 
face worldwide. 
</p>
<p> States should adopt specific measures to protect and preserve the rights to life and 
security of persons with albinism, as well as their right not to be subject to torture and ill-
treatment, and ensure their access to adequate health care, employment, education and 
justice. 
</p>
<p> 
 
</p>
<p>  
 * Late submission. 
</p>

