as a disability. Discrimination laws in Australia protect the rights of people with disabilities, including 
albinism (Albinism Fellowship of Australia submission). In Canada and the United States, persons 
with albinism are considered &#8220;legally blind&#8221; and thus as persons with disabilities according to 
</p>
